article.headline: Winthrop 82, High Point 68
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. -- Reggie Middleton hit four 3-pointers on his way to scoring 25 points to lead Winthrop to an 82-68 victory over High Point on Saturday night. Middleton led four Eagles (2-4, 1-1 Big South Conference) in double figures as Winthrop snapped a three-game losing streak with a strong second half. Winthrop was 13-for-24 from the field (54.2 percent) in the second half and pulled away from High Point (4-3, 1-1) after the Panthers took a 54-53 lead on Andre Jones' jumper with 8:14 left in the game. Middleton keyed a 10-0 run by scoring eight points -- including two 3-pointers -- with an assist on the other basket as the Eagles stretched their advantage to 63-54. Jones scored 13 points, Robbie Dreher added 11 and Gideon Gamble finished with 10 points for Winthrop, which outrebounded High Point 35-25. Nick Barbour and Eugene Harris scored 17 points each for the Panthers.
